## Understanding Through Fibonacci

Fibonacci means each number is the sum of the two before it.
0, 1, 1, 2, 3, 5, 8, 13, 21 ...
fib(6) = 8

### Code

```python
def fib(n):
    if n <= 1:                        # base case — covers 0 and 1
        return n
    return fib(n - 1) + fib(n - 2)  # two recursive calls
```

### Why this is dangerous

Fibonacci makes TWO recursive calls every time. So the number of
calls doubles at every level. This is what the call tree looks like
for fib(5):
                fib(5)
             /          \
       fib(4)            fib(3)
      /      \           /    \
   fib(3)  fib(2)    fib(2)  fib(1)
   /   \    /   \    /   \
fib(2) fib(1) ...  ...  ...

You can see fib(3) is being calculated twice, fib(2) multiple times.
This is a huge waste. The complexity becomes O(2ⁿ) which is extremely
slow for large inputs.

### Complexity

Time  : O(2ⁿ) — doubles with every level. Very slow!  
Space : O(n)  — maximum depth of the call stack at any point

---

## How to Fix Fibonacci — Memoization

The fix is simple. Store the answer the first time you calculate it.
Next time someone asks for the same value just return the stored answer
instead of recalculating everything again.

```python
def fib_memo(n, memo={}):
    if n <= 1:
        return n
    if n in memo:                              # already calculated
        return memo[n]
    memo[n] = fib_memo(n-1, memo) + fib_memo(n-2, memo)
    return memo[n]
```

Time  : O(n) — each value calculated only once now  
Space : O(n) — memo dictionary + call stack

This concept is called memoization. I will study it more deeply
later in dynamic programming. But even knowing it exists at day 2
feels useful.

---

## The Mistakes I Almost Made Today

Forgot to write return before the recursive call. The function
was returning None silently and I had no idea why. Always write
return in front of the recursive call.

I also thought making the input smaller by 1 each time would be
slow. But that is exactly how it is supposed to work. The base
case catches it before it goes negative.

