## What I Will Carry Forward

Recursion shows up everywhere later — in trees, graphs, and
backtracking problems. So understanding it deeply now instead of
just memorizing it is very important.

Every time I write a recursive function I will now ask:
1. What is my base case?
2. Am I making the input smaller?
3. Did I write return?
4. What is the space complexity of my call stack?
